4. Finally, we replace lists (i.e., ordered or unordered) with HTML lists. The listPattern variable matches any sequence of asterisks or hyphens followed by one or more word characters, and the `$2` backreference matches the contents of the list. The `\1` backreference matches the previous capturing group, so the function will match either an ordered list (`1.`) or an unordered list (`-`).

